body:
@NickeZ There's #1258 to aim exploring the expansion of command line parameters.

I'm also personally not a big fan of the idea to merge multiple configuration files together. I feel like the complexity here shouldn't be introduced to Alacritty, but to an external system instead.

Having different configuration files for different systems is certainly not something new to Alacritty. On Linux there's about a billion dotfile managers aimed at helping out with this, I personally think that just using git for that is a great solution. Using separate branches for separate systems or just using the stash for system-specific settings has worked extremely well for me.
